							p A prototype of a web application for cataloguing pixel art that inspires you, for reference when you make your own. It uses #[a(href="http://emberjs.com") Ember] for MVC, #[a(href="https://nodejs.org") Node] + #[a(href="http://expressjs.com") Express] for a simple RESTful API and #[a(href="https://mongodb.org") MongoDB] for the database. The demo here is just of the interface and the back-end functionality has been disabled. You can make changes but nothing is stored. The full version is #[a(href="https://github.com/stevecochrane/pixel-art-scrapbook") available on GitHub] but you&apos;ll need to run a local Node server to use it.
							p: a.button(href="pixel-art-scrapbook/", target="_blank") View a demo

